div.p:
The things you talk to have demonstrated about Telescopes [p. 56.] I have demonstrated already to be Impertinent;
and I am no ways concern'd in Them: I never denied, but that there was great difference in the Representations o •…
Objects made by Telescopes, as they are longer, or shorter, of purer, or of darker Metals, &c. And there is no doubt, but a great reason of the difference between Astronomers about the celestial Phaenomena, ariseth from the difference between the Telescopes they imploy. I never said, that they were All perfect and infallible in minute Particulars; But that all were not deceitful, and did not present to us meer Phantastical Objects, that had nothing Real: So that in all your Argumentations here, you have spent your Strength upon Shadows. Let the Reader compare, as you would have him, and judge.
